<doc id="678165" wikidata="Q1562288" url="?curid=678165" title="Aleksandar Žiljak">
<text>Aleksandar Žiljak (born 19 June 1963) is a science fiction and fantasy writer and illustrator from Zagreb, Croatia. In 2006, he co-edited &quot;Ad Astra&quot;, an anthology of Croatian SF stories, which covers period from 1976 to 2006, and he co-edits Croatian literary SF journal &quot;Ubiq&quot;.

Žiljak is the winner of five SFERA Awards, three for Best Story and two for Best Illustration. His story &quot;An Evening In The City Coffeehouse, With Lydia On My Mind&quot; was included in &quot;The Apex Book of World SF&quot; (2009).

