==Education==
As per the 2011 census, the average literacy rate in South India is approximately 80%, considerably higher than the Indian national average of 74%, with Kerala having the highest literacy rate of 93.91%. South India is home to some of the nation&#x27;s largest and most prominent public and private institutions of higher education.

